{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeClassRef\/addPrivate(privateSize:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeClassRef","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeClassRef\/TypeClassProtocol-Implementations"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glibobject\/typeclassref\/addprivate(privatesize:)"]}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"extendedModule":"GLibObject","platforms":[],"title":"addPrivate(privateSize:)","roleHeading":"Instance Method","externalID":"s:10GLibObject17TypeClassProtocolPAAE10addPrivate11privateSizeySi_tF::SYNTHESIZED::s:10GLibObject12TypeClassRefV","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"addPrivate"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"privateSize"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"modules":[{"name":"GLibObject"}],"symbolKind":"method","role":"symbol"},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Registers a private structure for an instantiatable type."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"addPrivate","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"privateSize","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"When an object is allocated, the private structures for","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the type and all of its parent types are allocated"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"sequentially in the same memory block as the public"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"structures, and are zero-filled."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Note that the accumulated size of the private structures of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a type and all its parent types cannot exceed 64 KiB."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This function should be called in the type’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class_init()"},{"text":" function.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"The private structure can be retrieved using the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"G_TYPE_INSTANCE_GET_PRIVATE()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" macro."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following example shows attaching a private structure"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"MyObjectPrivate to an object MyObject defined in the standard","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"GObject fashion in the type’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"class_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" function."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note the use of a structure member “priv” to avoid the overhead"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of repeatedly calling "},{"code":"MY_OBJECT_GET_PRIVATE()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"(C Language Example):"}]},{"syntax":"C","code":["typedef struct _MyObject        MyObject;","typedef struct _MyObjectPrivate MyObjectPrivate;","","struct _MyObject {"," GObject parent;",""," MyObjectPrivate *priv;","};","","struct _MyObjectPrivate {","  int some_field;","};","","static void","my_object_class_init (MyObjectClass *klass)","{","  g_type_class_add_private (klass, sizeof (MyObjectPrivate));","}","","static void","my_object_init (MyObject *my_object)","{","  my_object->priv = G_TYPE_INSTANCE_GET_PRIVATE (my_object,","                                                 MY_TYPE_OBJECT,","                                                 MyObjectPrivate);","  \/\/ my_object->priv->some_field will be automatically initialised to 0","}","","static int","my_object_get_some_field (MyObject *my_object)","{","  MyObjectPrivate *priv;","","  g_return_val_if_fail (MY_IS_OBJECT (my_object), 0);","","  priv = my_object->priv;","","  return priv->some_field;","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"add_private is deprecated:"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Use the G_ADD_PRIVATE() macro with the ","type":"text"},{"code":"G_DEFINE_*","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"family of macros to add instance private data to a type"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"references":{"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/TypeClassRef":{"role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"TypeClassRef"}],"title":"TypeClassRef","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeClassRef","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An opaque structure used as the base of all classes."}],"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"TypeClassRef","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/typeclassref"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/TypeClassRef/TypeClassProtocol-Implementations":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeClassRef\/TypeClassProtocol-Implementations","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/typeclassref\/typeclassprotocol-implementations","title":"TypeClassProtocol Implementations","role":"collectionGroup","abstract":[],"type":"topic","kind":"article"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject":{"abstract":[],"